{
  "texts": [
    "Bradford's Law suggests that a small number of journals are central to a specific research field.",
    "[20] As illustrated in Fig. 3, the ten journals highlighted in Table 6 form this core group, accounting for approximately one-third of the entire collection's documents.",
    "Table 6 provides details on these top ten periodicals, each contributing one or more articles to our bibliographic collection.",
    "Notably, RADIOLOGY is the most preferred journal, with 57 articles, followed by EURO-PEAN RADIOLOGY and IEEE TRANSACTIONS ON MEDICAL IMAGING, with 40 and 32 articles, respectively.",
    "Regarding the H-index, which measures the number of published articles (h) that have been cited at least h times, IEEE TRANSAC-TIONS ON MEDICAL IMAGING leads with an H-index of 24 and an impressive 4,254 total citations."
  ]
}